{"title_page": "Laurent Sauvagnac", "text_new": "{{multiple issues|\n{{Orphan|date=April 2014}}\n{{BLP sources|date=April 2014}}\n{{advert|date=August 2015}}\n}}\n'''Laurent Sauvagnac''' (born June 19, 1970 in Paris) is a French film score composer<ref>{{cite web|url=http://madame.lefigaro.fr/feminin/laurent-sauvagnac-38-ans-091210-25794|title=Laurent Sauvagnac, 38 ans|date=1 December 2008|publisher=- Le Figaro - Madame|language=French|accessdate=3 October 2014}}</ref> and a sound designer who graduated from the [[Berklee College of Music]] (Boston).\n\n==Biography==\n\nAfter his graduation (Master II) in Paris, he left France in 1996 for Boston to study at the Berklee College of Music and specialize in film scoring and perfect his piano jazz.\n\nSauvagnac began his career in 2000 in Paris, creating original music for [[Cartier (jeweler)|Cartier]], [[Louis Vuitton]] and Henessy. He is known for the film scoring of the [[L\u2019Oreal]], Pond's, [[Bioderma]] and [[Dolce & Gabbana]] commercials in collaboration with  X-Track (music placement & online radio).\n\nIn 2002, he composed and produced the music of a fashion show for [[Jean-Paul Gaultier]] mixing Strauss waltz with electronic music. During the same year, Sauvagnac chose to pair up with the film score composer Stephane Zidi for a few projects. \nThe duo created original music for : Champion, Korean movie by Kyung-Taek Kwak (with the Philarmonic Orchestra of Prague), Tel \u00e9pris by [[Fabien Onteniente]] (Kien production, 2001), Comme deux gouttes d\u2019eau (Demd prod, 2002), Laura, le compte \u00e0 rebours a commenc\u00e9 (Samla prod, 2006), La Lance de la destin\u00e9e and La Main blanche (Vab prod, 2007), La L\u00e9gende des trois cl\u00e9s (Nelka films, 2008), \u00ab Cellule Identit\u00e9 \u00bb (Demd, 2008), Brigade Navarro (JLA, 2008), L\u2019Amour vache and 10 jours pour s\u2019aimer (Bankizz, 2010), L\u2019Internat (Gaumont-Leonis, 2009), La Maison de Rocheville, Je vous aime tr\u00e8s beaucoup (Nelka films), \u00ab Victoire Bonot \u00bb (Vab, 2010), \u00ab Clara \u00bb (Cin\u00e9t\u00e9v\u00e9, 2009), Le Chasseur (Son et Lumi\u00e8re, 2010), Les Ripoux (Panama, 2010), L\u2019Amour encore plus vache (Bankiz, 2010), Le Sang de la vigne (Telecip, 2011), Police District for Capa Drama, Engrenages for [[Canal +]]. A short film : 36e sous sol by P.H Debi\u00e8s. They also composed the music of a documentary about Paris called Sur les toits de Paris, le monde des couleurs - G\u00e9d\u00e9on produced by  Electric Picture.\n \nSince 2005, Sauvagnac created H\u00e9ho Design with Marc Debi\u00e8s, working as a sound architect and an artistic director. It is an essential component of perception of space, time and directly affects the state, behavior, welfare, or stress of the user. With this sound material, Heho designs and creates perceptions to improve the architecture, environment and communication according to the objectives and needs.\nH\u00e9ho has been working for the Luxury Hotels [[Ritz-Carlton Hotel Company|Ritz]], [[Plaza Ath\u00e9n\u00e9e]], Le [[Fouquet's]] Barriere or [[British Airways]]. Since 2013, H\u00e9ho has been working with [[Unibail-Rodamco]] in jumbo malls like So Ouest or Aeroville. Sauvagnac and his team created an original concept with spatialized sound events getting through 12 speakers in a gigantic glass roof.\n\nRunning parallel with music composition, Sauvagnac created a music publishing company, M Factory Publishing, in 2014, thanks to the discovery of heterogeneous artists, new talents, producers and beatmakers. The company already placed several sound tracks on short films, full-length movies and teasers. He also runs M Factory Studio with Pierre Lemariey as sound engineer and producer associate. They produce, distribute albums and manage artists careers.\n\n== Movies Soundtracks by So and Zi  ==\n\n*2013 TV series Engrenages - saison 3 & 4 (St\u00e9phane Zidi/Canal+/Sons et Lumi\u00e8res)\n*Dangereuses Retrouvailles de J\u00e9r\u00f4me Debusscheres avec Antoine de Caunes\n*2011 S\u00e9rie Victoire Bonnot(M6)\n*pour Bankizz production L'Amour vache, L'Amour encore plus vache, 10 jours pour s'aimer (M6)\n*Une cible dans le dos-Bernard Uzan\n*Ripoux anonymes (Claude Zidi / TF1)\n*TV series Le Sang de la vigne avec Pierre Arditi\n*2010 S\u00e9rie La Maison des Rochevilles avec Alexandre Brasseur (Nelka Films)\n*2009 TV series Le Chasseur (FR2/Son et Lumiere) - O.Cuche\n*TV series L'Internat (Marathon/Gaumont TV)\n*TV series Brigade Navarro (TF1)\n*2008 TV series Engrenages - Saison 2 (St\u00e9phane Zidi/Canal+/sons et Lumi\u00e8res)\n*TV series Sur le fil - Saison2 (FR2/sons et Lumi\u00e8res)\n*TV series Revivre (Arte/Nelka films) - H.Bouzaglo\n*TV series Brigade Navarro (TF1/JLA) - P. Davin\n*Mini TV series Clara (FR2/cin\u00e9t\u00e9v\u00e9) - S.Gral\n*TV series La Main blanche (TF1/JLA) - Dennis Berry\n*TV series / documentary French-Australian Le Monde des couleurs (Arte/G\u00e9d\u00e9on)\n*2007 Mini TV series La L\u00e9gende des trois cl\u00e9s (M6/Nelka films) - P.Dewolf\n*Mini TV series Le Canap\u00e9 rouge (TF1/Dajma) - A. Castello\n*TV series Sur le fil (FR2/sons et lumi\u00e8res) - F.Berthe\n*TV series Cellule Identit\u00e9 (M6/DEMD prod) - S.Kappes\n*Feature film C\u00f4te \u00e0 c\u00f4te (Nelka films) - H. Bouzaglo\n*Mini TV series Sa raison d'\u00eatre (Merlin Prod/FR2) - Renaud Bertrand\n*TV series La Lance de la Destin\u00e9e (JLA/M6) - Dennis Berry\n*         \u2022      Short Film 2006 Mesrine (TF1) - A. S\u00e9lignac\n*TV series Engrenages (Canal+/Sons et lumi\u00e8res) - P. Triboix/P. Chaumeil\n*Mini TV series La Promeneuse d'oiseaux (FR2/Nelka Films) - J. Otmesguine\n*Feature Film Janem Janem (Nelka Films) - H. Bouzaglo\n*Short film La Reine Sylvie (cin\u00e9t\u00e9v\u00e9/FR3) - Renaud Bertrand\n*Short film Camping Paradis(JLA/TF1) - D.Albert\n*TV series Laura (M6/Sama prod) - J-T Filippe\n*         \u2022  \tShort film 2005 Je t'aime \u00e0 te tuer (TF1/ Dajma prod.)\n*Commercials INPES pour le mieux manger\n*Short film Ils voulaient tuer De Gaulle (TF1/Capa Drama) - J-T Filippe\n*Feature film Les Irr\u00e9ductibles (Magnificat Films) - Renaud Bertrand\n*Short film Comme deux gouttes d'eau (FR3/ DEMD prod) - Stephane Kurk\n*Documentary Charles&Camilla (France 5/Online Prod)\n*Documentary Un patrimoine encombrant (France5/Online Prod)\n*Feature Film 3 Couples en qu\u00eate d\u2019orages (Nelka Films/Mazel Prod.) - Jacques Otmezguine\n*Festival of Auxerre, in competition, Sarlat et Paris\n*Pilot for TV Serie Engrenages (Canal+/Son et Lumi\u00e8re) - J-T Filippe\n*Mini TV series Le Triporteur de Belleville (France 2 /Nelka Films) - St\u00e9phane Kurck\n*Symphonic arrangements symphoniques for the second album of [[Manu Lanvin]] (Warner Music)\n*Short Film La Nourrice (FR3/Cin\u00e9t\u00e9v\u00e9) - R. Bertrand\n*Award for the best French TV Drama soundtrack \n*T\u00e9l\u00e9film Mortelle Conviction (M6/GMT Prod.) - J-T Fillipe\n*Arrangements for strings for the band N\u00f2rd (Sony/Universal)\n*2002 Fashion shows J.-P. Gaultier\n*2 fun CD Roms ludiques pour Gallimard Jeunesse\n*TV Series La Ligne noire (M6/Capa Drama) - J-T Fillipe\n*TV Series Police District (13 \u00e0 18) (M6/Capa Drama) - J-T Fillipe / J. Enrico\n*Feature Film Champion (production Americano-Korean) - recorded with the symphonic orchestra of Prague\n*Documentary Les Toits de Paris (La 5/Arte/Ampersand)\n*2001 TV Series Police District (7 \u00e0 12) (M6/Capa Drama) - J-T Fillipe / M. Boursiniac\n*Short Film Tel \u00e9pris (France 2/Kien Prod.) - F. Onteniente\n*Arrangements the opening of the album Atylantos produced by Jean-Patrick Capdevielle (Sony Musique)\n*TV Series Police District (1 to 6)\u00bb (M6/Capa Drama) - O. Chavarot\n*Documentary CIO 2000 (Arte/Dune Prod.)\n*2001-2013 commercial movies (Kellog's, D&G, L'Or\u00e9al, Axe, Lucien Barri\u00e8re, Chivas, Cacharel, Gucci, Cartier, Orange...)\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{IMDb name|1580616}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Sauvagnac, Laurent}}\n[[Category:1970 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:French composers]]\n[[Category:French male composers]]\n", "text_old": "{{multiple issues|\n{{Orphan|date=April 2014}}\n{{BLP sources|date=April 2014}}\n{{advert|date=August 2015}}\n}}\n'''Laurent Sauvagnac''' (born June 19, 1970 in Paris) is a French film score composer<ref>{{cite web|url=http://madame.lefigaro.fr/feminin/laurent-sauvagnac-38-ans-091210-25794|title=Laurent Sauvagnac, 38 ans|date=1 December 2008|publisher=- Le Figaro - Madame|language=French|accessdate=3 October 2014}}</ref> and a sound designer who graduated from the [[Berklee College of Music]] (Boston).\n\n==Biography==\n\nAfter his graduation (Master II) in Paris, he left France in 1996 for Boston to study at the Berklee College of Music and specialize in film scoring and perfect his piano jazz.\n\nSauvagnac began his career in 2000 in Paris, creating original music for [[Cartier (jeweler)|Cartier]], [[Louis Vuitton]] and Henessy. He is known for the film scoring of the [[L\u2019Oreal]], Pond\u2019s, [[Bioderma]] and [[Dolce & Gabbana]] commercials in collaboration with  X-Track (music placement & online radio).\n\nIn 2002, he composed and produced the music of a fashion show for [[Jean-Paul Gaultier]] mixing Strauss waltz with electronic music. During the same year, Sauvagnac chose to pair up with the film score composer Stephane Zidi for a few projects. \nThe duo created original music for : Champion, Korean movie by Kyung-Taek Kwak (with the Philarmonic Orchestra of Prague), Tel \u00e9pris by [[Fabien Onteniente]] (Kien production, 2001), Comme deux gouttes d\u2019eau (Demd prod, 2002), Laura, le compte \u00e0 rebours a commenc\u00e9 (Samla prod, 2006), La Lance de la destin\u00e9e and La Main blanche (Vab prod, 2007), La L\u00e9gende des trois cl\u00e9s (Nelka films, 2008), \u00ab Cellule Identit\u00e9 \u00bb (Demd, 2008), Brigade Navarro (JLA, 2008), L\u2019Amour vache and 10 jours pour s\u2019aimer (Bankizz, 2010), L\u2019Internat (Gaumont-Leonis, 2009), La Maison de Rocheville, Je vous aime tr\u00e8s beaucoup (Nelka films), \u00ab Victoire Bonot \u00bb (Vab, 2010), \u00ab Clara \u00bb (Cin\u00e9t\u00e9v\u00e9, 2009), Le Chasseur (Son et Lumi\u00e8re, 2010), Les Ripoux (Panama, 2010), L\u2019Amour encore plus vache (Bankiz, 2010), Le Sang de la vigne (Telecip, 2011), Police District for Capa Drama, Engrenages for [[Canal +]]. A short film : 36e sous sol by P.H Debi\u00e8s. They also composed the music of a documentary about Paris called Sur les toits de Paris, le monde des couleurs - G\u00e9d\u00e9on produced by  Electric Picture.\n \nSince 2005, Sauvagnac created H\u00e9ho Design with Marc Debi\u00e8s, working as a sound architect and an artistic director. It is an essential component of perception of space, time and directly affects the state, behavior, welfare, or stress of the user. With this sound material, Heho designs and creates perceptions to improve the architecture, environment and communication according to the objectives and needs.\nH\u00e9ho has been working for the Luxury Hotels [[Ritz-Carlton Hotel Company|Ritz]], [[Plaza Ath\u00e9n\u00e9e]], Le [[Fouquet's]] Barriere or [[British Airways]]. Since 2013, H\u00e9ho has been working with [[Unibail-Rodamco]] in jumbo malls like So Ouest or Aeroville. Sauvagnac and his team created an original concept with spatialized sound events getting through 12 speakers in a gigantic glass roof.\n\nRunning parallel with music composition, Sauvagnac created a music publishing company, M Factory Publishing, in 2014, thanks to the discovery of heterogeneous artists, new talents, producers and beatmakers. The company already placed several sound tracks on short films, full-length movies and teasers. He also runs M Factory Studio with Pierre Lemariey as sound engineer and producer associate. They produce, distribute albums and manage artists careers.\n\n== Movies Soundtracks b