ennium Eagle'', Magazine of [[Bedford Modern School]], Winter 1999, reprinted (with amendments) August 2004, p.42</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cambridgeassessment.org.uk/about-us/who-we-are/our-leadership/saul-nasse/|title=Saul Nass\u00e9|publisher=|accessdate=3 March 2016}}</ref>\n* [[Russell Barnes]] (born 1968), television producer (''[[The Enemies of Reason]]'', ''[[The Genius of Charles Darwin]]'')<ref name=\"Underwood 2010\"/>\n* [[David Jubb (theatre director)|David Jubb]] (born 1970), theatre director and chief executive of the [[Battersea Arts Centre]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.debretts.com/people-of-today/profile/23491/David-JUBB |title=David Jubb, Esq Authorised Biography \u2013 Debrett's People of Today |work=debretts.com |accessdate=29 January 2015 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141110041050/http://www.debretts.com/people-of-today/profile/23491/David-JUBB |archivedate=10 November 2014 }}</ref><ref>''[[Who's Who (UK)|Who's Who]]'', Published by [[A & C Black]], 2020, online edition</ref>\n* [[Russell Howard]] (born 1980), comedian and presenter (''[[Russell Howard's Good News]]'')<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.debretts.com/people-of-today/profile/55201/Russell-Joseph-HOWARD|title=Mr Russell Howard Authorised Biography \u2013 Debrett's People of Today|work=debretts.com|accessdate=29 January 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://russell-magic-cock-howard.tumblr.com/russellhoward|title=Russell Howard's Fruity Fansite|publisher=|accessdate=25 February 2016}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/?id=oAM7DwAAQBAJ&pg=PP3&dq=debrett's+people+of+today+2017#v=onepage&q=russell+howARD|title=People of Today 2017|first=Lucy|last=Hume|date=5 October 2017|publisher=Debrett's|via=Google Books|isbn=9781999767037}}</ref>\n* [[Leon Parris]] (born 1981), writer, composer, musician and actor (''[[Wolfboy]]'')<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/education/education-news/education-rise-of-the-fallen-1187285.html|title=Education: Rise of 'The Fallen'|work=The Independent|accessdate=30 January 2015|date=1998-11-26}}</ref>\n* [[Jeremy Irvine]] (born 1990), UK and Hollywood actor (''[[War Horse (film)|War Horse]]'', ''[[Now Is Good]]'', ''[[Great Expectations (2012 film)|Great Expectations]]'', ''[[The Railway Man (film)|The Railway Man]]'')<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bedfordshire-news.co.uk/horsing-talented-blockbuster-role-student-landed/story-21735089-detail/story.html|title=There is no horsing around for talented a blockbuster role student who landed|work=Bedfordshire News|accessdate=30 January 2015}}</ref>\n* [[Sope Dirisu]] (born 1991), stage, television and film actor<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bedmod.co.uk/2016/04/21/show-business-success-for-obms/|title=Show business success for OBMs|work=Bedford Modern|date=2016-04-21}}</ref>\n* [[Suhani Gandhi]] (born 1994), model and actress<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bedfordtoday.co.uk/news/community-news/talented-student-s-passage-to-india-1-5863917|title=Talented student's passage to India|work=bedfordtoday.co.uk|accessdate=30 January 2015}}</ref>\n\n==Adventurers, aviators, exiles and prisoners of war==\n[[File:John Percy Farrar.jpg|thumb|115px|right|[[John Percy Farrar|Capt. Percy Farrar DSO FGS]]]]\n* [[John Percy Farrar]] [[Distinguished Service Order|DSO]] (1857\u20131929), soldier, mountaineer, President of the [[Alpine Club]], Member of the [[Mount Everest Committee]]<ref name=\"auto\">H.E. Vipan, ''Register of the Old Boys of Bedford Modern School''</ref><ref>Obituary in the ''Bedfordshire Times'', 22 February 1929, p.9</ref>\n* [[Sir Reginald Wolseley, 10th Baronet]] (1872\u20131933), dubbed the elevator [[baronet]]<ref>Kelly's Handbook to the Titled, Landed and Official Classes, Published 1928</ref>\n* [[Henry Evered Haymes|Captain and Bimbashi Henry Haymes]] [[Venerable Order of St John|SBStJ]] [[Royal College of Surgeons|MRCS]] [[LRCP]] (1872\u20131904), surgeon, an original explorer of the [[Bahr el Ghazal (region of South Sudan)|Bahr-el-Ghazal]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dnw.co.uk/auction-archive/catalogue-archive/lot.php?auction_id=230&lot_id=77178|title=Lot 31, The Allan and Janet Woodliffe Collection of Medals... (18 May 2011) \u2013 Dix Noonan Webb|work=dnw.co.uk|accessdate=30 January 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141223142200/http://www.dnw.co.uk/auction-archive/catalogue-archive/lot.php?auction_id=230&lot_id=77178|archive-date=23 December 2014|url-status=dead|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n* [[George E.M. Kelly]] (1878\u20131911), early aviator in the [[Aeronautical Division, US Signal Corps]]<ref name=\"auto\"/> \n* [[Aeneas Mackintosh|Captain Aeneas Lionel Acton Mackintosh]] (1879\u20131916), [[Heroic Age of Antarctic Exploration|Antarctic explorer]], commander of the [[Ross Sea party]] expedition<ref name=\"Underwood 1981\"/>\n* [[W.A.B. Goodall]] (1880\u20131941), [[castaway]], described as 'the ruler of the world's tiniest kingdom': [[Pulau Sarimbun]], [[Straits of Johore]]<ref>H.E. Vipan, ''A Register of the Old Boys of the Bedford Modern School'' (Bedford, no date), p. 47</ref> \n* [[Duncan Alexander Eliott Mackintosh]] (1884\u20131966), 31st Chief of [[Chattan Confederation|Clan Chattan]] (1942\u201366)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thepeerage.com/p45058.htm|title=- Person Page 45058|work=thepeerage.com|accessdate=19 January 2015}}</ref>\n* [[Wilfrid Thomas Reid]] [[Royal Aeronautical Society|FRAeS]] (1887\u20131968), aircraft designer and a pioneer of the Canadian aircraft industry<ref name=\"Underwood 2010\"/>\n* [[P.C.B. Newington]] (1888\u20131964), author of a [[Cookbook|cookbook]] celebrating Malaysian food, conceived while starving as a [[prisoner of war]]<ref name=\"google.com4\">{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/?id=vJcZAAAAMAAJ&dq=He+was+educated+at+Bedford+Modern+School&q=philip+Newington|title=Malaysia|accessdate=13 November 2015|year=1964}}</ref>\n* [[Frederick Williamson]] [[Order of the Indian Empire|CIE]] (1891\u20131935), explorer, founder member of the Himalayan Club<ref name=\"Underwood 1981\"/>\n* [[Dick Howe|Captain Richard 'Dick' Howe]] [[Order of the British Empire|MBE]] [[Military Cross|MC]] (1916\u20131981), Escape Officer at [[Colditz Castle]] during [[World War II]] (1942\u20131945)<ref name=\"auto1\">{{cite web|url=http://www.roll-of-honour.com/Bedfordshire/BedfordModernSchoolMemorials.html|title=Roll of Honour \u2013 Bedfordshire \u2013 Bedford Modern School Memorials|work=roll-of-honour.com|accessdate=30 January 2015}}</ref><ref>Obituary in ''[[The Times]]'', ''Captain Richard Howe'', 4 June 1981, p.16</ref>\n* [[Desmond 'Dizzy' de Villiers]] [[Air Force Cross (United Kingdom)|AFC]] (1922\u20131976), [[test pilot|chief test pilot]] at [[de Havilland]] and [[English Electric]]<ref name=\"Underwood 2010\"/>\n\n==Architecture, art and design==\n[[File:Statue of Josiah Conder in the University of Tokyo 0101.jpg|thumb|115px|right|[[Josiah Conder (architect)|Josiah Conder, statue at the University of Tokyo]]]]\n* [[Josiah Conder (architect)|Josiah Conder]] (1852\u20131920), architect who designed the ''[[Rokumeikan]]'' and other public buildings in Tokyo<ref name=\"Underwood 1981\"/>\n* [[Henry John Sylvester Stannard]] [[Royal Society of British Artists|RBA]] [[Royal Society of Arts|FRSA]] (1870\u20131951), [[Watercolor painting|watercolour]] artist<ref name=\"Underwood 1981\"/>\n*[[Sydney Morgan Eveleigh]] (1870-1947), architect in Vancouver<ref>H.E. Vipan, 'A Register of the Old Boys of the Bedford Modern School', (Bedford, no date), p. 38.</ref>\n* [[Hugh Patrick Guarin Maule|Major Hugh Patrick Guarin Maule]] [[Distinguished Service Order|DSO]] [[Military Cross|MC]] [[Royal Institute of British Architects|FRIBA]] (1873\u20131940), architect ([[Royal Veterinary College]] in London)<ref name=\"Who Was Who\" />\n* [[George Loraine Stampa]] (1875\u20131951), artist, contributor to [[Punch (magazine)|Punch]] and other illustrated papers and magazines<ref name=\"Underwood 1981\"/>\n* [[W. B. Stonebridge|Walter Stonebridge]] [[Royal Institute of British Architects|FRIBA]] (1879\u20131962), Diocesan Architect for [[Ely, Cambridgeshire|Ely]], [[St Albans]] and [[Bedford]]<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/?id=GkThQYLb3ZUC&pg=PA714&lpg=PA714&dq=walter+butler+stonebridge#v=onepage&q=walter%20butler%20stonebridge|title=Directory of British Architects, 1834-1914|publisher=|accessdate=8 May 2016|isbn=9780826455147|date=2001-12-20|last1=Brodie|first1=Antonia|last2=Library|first2=British Architectural|last3=Architects|first3=Royal Institute of British}}</ref>\n* [[Algernon Winter Rose]] [[Military Cross|MC]] (1885\u20131918), architect<ref name=\"Underwood 1981\"/><ref>{{cite book |chapter=Rose, Algernon Winter, 1885-1918 |chapterurl={{Google books|GkThQYLb3ZUC|page=503|plainurl=yes}} |page=503 |editor1-first=Antonia |editor1-last=Brodie |title=Directory of British Architects, 1834-1914: Vol. 2 (L-Z) |year=2001 |isbn=9780826455147 }}</ref>\n* [[Kenneth Alexander (photographer)|Kenneth Alexander]] (1887\u20131975), Hollywood photographer for [[United Artists]] and [[21st Century Fox]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mocavo.com/Men-of-Hawaii-Being-a-Biographical-Reference-Library-Complete-and-Comprehensive-Volume-1/896284/21|title=Men of Hawaii: Being a Biographical Reference Library, Complete and Comprehensive|work=Mocavo|accessdate=30 January 2015}}</ref>\n* [[Robert Tor Russell]] [[Order of the Indian Empire|CIE]] [[Distinguished Service Order|DSO]] (1888\u20131972), Chief Architect to the Government of India<ref name=\"auto\"/><ref>''The Eagle'', Vol. XIII no. 4 (March 1917), p. 64</ref>\n* [[Thomas Ford (architect)|Thomas Francis Ford]] [[FRIBA]] (1891\u20131971), [[Diocese|Diocesan]] Architect for [[Southwark]] and a translator of the [[New Testament]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.biblecollectors.org/biographies/ford_brothers.htm|title=The Ford Brothers|work=biblecollectors.org|accessdate=30 January 2015}}</ref>\n* [[Alexander Girard]] (1907\u20131993), textile designer and interior architect<ref>''Eagle News'', The Magazine of the Old Bedford Modernians' Club, Issue 114, Winter 2016/17</ref>\n* [[Victor Farrar|Victor Farrar RIBA PPFAS FRSA]] (1930\u20132007), architect<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://bedsarchivescat.bedford.gov.uk/Details/archive/110023155|title=Bedfordshire Archives Service Catalogue &#124; Details|website=bedsarchivescat.bedford.gov.uk}}</ref> \n* [[Dennis Sharp]] (1933\u20132010), architect, professor, curator, historian, author and editor<ref>{{Cite newspaper|url=https://www.theguardian.com/artanddesign/2010/jun/21/dennis-sharp-obituary|title=Dennis Sharp obituary|journal=The Guardian|accessdate=30 January 2015|date=2010-06-21|last1=Rykwert|first1=Joseph}}</ref>\n* [[Steve Gibbons (designer)|Steve Gibbons]] (born 1956), graphic designer<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.debretts.com/people-of-today/profile/8043/Stephen-John-GIBBONS|title=Stephen Gibbons, Esq Authorised Biography \u2013 Debrett's People of Today|work=debretts.com|accessdate=1 April 2015|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://archive.is/20150404123809/http://www.debretts.com/people-of-today/profile/8043/Stephen-John-GIBBONS|archivedate=4 April 2015|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n* [[Alex Chinneck]] (born 1984), sculptor and installation artist<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bedfordshire-news.co.uk/pictures/Artist-Alex-Chinneck-gives-Bedford-College/pictures-25862008-detail/pictures.html|title=Artist, Alex Chinneck, gives Bedford College students a sneak preview of his work in 2015|work=Bedfordshire News|accessdate=30 January 2015}}</ref>\n\n==Armed forces==\n[[File:VCGeorgeGodfreyMassyWheeler.jpg|thumb|115px|right|[[George Godfrey Massy Wheeler|Major George Wheeler VC]]]]\n[[File:HD Harvey-Kelly.jpg|thumb|115px|right|[[H.D. Harvey-Kelly|H.D. Harvey-Kelly DSO]]]]\n[[File:James Meldrum Knox DSO (1878\u20131918).jpg|thumb|115px|right|[[James Meldrum Knox|Lt-Col. James Knox DSO*]]]]\n[[File:First World War Memorial statue in front of Bank of Montreal.JPG|thumb|115px|right|[[Wynn Bagnall|Capt. Wynn Bagnall MC]], statue at [[Winnipeg]], Canada]]\n[[File:Admiral Horlick.jpg|thumb|115px|right|[[Ted Horlick|Sir Edwin Horlick KBE]]]]\n\n===Air Force===\n* [[George Marshall Griffith|Wing Commander George Marshall Griffith]] (1877\u20131946), Commandant of the [[Royal Flying Corps]] in India<ref name=\"autogenerated48\">{{cite web|url=https://livesofthefirstworldwar.iwm.org.uk/community/5183/?page=48 |title=Community: Bedford Modern School - List of Old Bedford Modernians serving in HM Forces 1914 - 1918. &#124; Lives of the First World War |publisher=Livesofthefirstworldwar.iwm.org.uk |date= |accessdate=2020-04-05}}</ref>\n* [[Percy Robert Clifford Groves|Brigadier-General Percy Robert Clifford Groves]] [[Order of the Bath|CB]] [[Order of St Michael and St George|CMG]] [[Distinguished Service Order|DSO]] (1878\u20131959), Air Strategist<ref name=\"Underwood 1981\" />\n* [[Robert Dickinson Oxland|Air Vice-Marshal Robert Dickinson Oxland]] [[Order of the Bath|CB]] [[Order of the British Empire|CBE]] (1889\u20131959), Group Commander in [[Bomber Command]] (1943\u201344)<ref name=\"Who Was Who\" />\n* [[Edye Rolleston Manning|Air Commodore Edye Rolleston Manning]] [[Order of the British Empire|CBE]] [[Distinguished Service Order|DSO]] [[Military Cross|MC]] (1889\u20131957), senior officer in the [[Royal Air Force]] during [[World War II]]<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/?id=A1AfAQAAMAAJ&q=DSO+bedford+modern&dq=DSO+bedford+modern|title=The Aeroplane|accessdate=14 November 2015|year=1935}}</ref><ref>Obituary in ''[[The Times]]'', ''Air CDRE. E.J. Manning'', 29 April 1957, p.12</ref>\n* [[Charles Henry Elliott-Smith|Air Commodore Charles Henry Elliott-Smith]] [[Air Force Cross (United Kingdom)|AFC]] (1889\u20131994), senior officer in the [[Royal Air Force]]<ref name=\"autogenerated49\">{{cite web|url=https://livesofthefirstworldwar.iwm.org.uk/community/5183/?page=49 |title=Community: Bedford