936), Commander, 1/5th [[Staffordshire Rangers|North Staffordshire Regiment]], 1/5th [[Sherwood Foresters]]<ref name=\"Who Was Who\" /><ref>War Honours Won By Old Boys, Bedford Modern School, Published by H.W. Robinson, [[Bedford]], 1931</ref>\n* [[Wynn Bagnall|Captain Wynn Bagnall]] [[Military Cross|MC]] (1890\u20131931), [[Canadian Field Artillery]], model for a statue by [[James Earle Fraser (sculptor)|James Fraser]] in [[Winnipeg, Manitoba]]<ref>''The Eagle'' Vol. XII no. 9 (December 2015),p. 338</ref>\n* [[Melville Rysdale Ten Broeke|Lieutenant-Colonel Melville Ten Broeke]] [[Military Cross|MC&bar]] (1891\u20131963), commander of [[Princess Patricia's Canadian Light Infantry|Princess Patricia's Canadian Light Infantry Regiment]]<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/?id=je2Jz_1c21sC&pg=PA719&lpg=PA719&dq=ten+broeke+vancouver+imperial#v=onepage&q=ten%20broeke%20vancouver%20imperial|title=Imperial Vancouver Island|accessdate=13 March 2015|isbn=9781450059633|last1=Bosher|first1=J. F.|date=April 2010}}</ref>\n* [[Leonard Arthur Hawes|Major-General L.A. Hawes]] [[Order of the British Empire|CBE]] [[Distinguished Service Order|DSO]] [[Military Cross|MC]] [[Deputy Lieutenant|DL]] (1892\u20131986), Commanded the transport to France of the [[British Expeditionary Force (World War II)|BEF]] during [[World War I]]<ref name=\"Who Was Who\" />\n* [[W.C.V. Galwey|Brigadier W.C.V. Galwey]] [[Order of the British Empire|OBE]] [[Military Cross|MC&bar]] (1897\u20131977), senior officer who served in [[World War I]] and [[World War II]]<ref name=\"Burke's Irish Family Records\" >Hugh Montgomery-Massingberd, ''Burke's Irish Family Records'' London, U.K.: Burkes Peerage Ltd, 1976</ref>\n* [[Ernest Dynes|Brigadier Ernest Dynes]] [[Order of the British Empire|CBE]] (1903\u20131968) was [[Aide-de-camp]] to HM Queen [[Elizabeth II]] (1955\u201357)<ref name=\"Who Was Who\" />\n* [[Thomas Henry Scott Galletly|Brigadier Thomas Henry Scott Galletly]] [[Distinguished Service Order|DS